stickers.name: Sticker | To B or not to B

agents.name: Bloody Darryl The Strapped | The Professionals
agents.description: Before he was leader of the heist gang 'The Professionals' Sir Bloody Darryl was more simply called, Bloody Darryl. Still your friendly neighborhood psychopath in every sense of the word. Not actually Australian according to Australians. \n\n I'm just gonna give them a bit of Razzle Dazzle.

agents.name: 'Blueberries' Buckshot | NSWC SEAL
agents.description:
Known as SEAL Team's "WeaponsSommelier" Buckshot has thoroughly field-tested and reviewed almost every available military weapon in staggering depth. ST6 relies on Buckshot's knowledge of lesser-known guns for edge case advantages in ground based operations.

Seen here sporting the classic NUE Type 1 uniform otherwise known as 'blueberries'. 

 They talk to me. The guns. They have feelings.

agents.name: 'Two Times' McCoy | TACP Cavalry
agents.description:
'Two Times' McCoy earned his nickname by completing TACP's field training twice. Official records mark this up to a scheduling mix-up, but his teammates report restraining him from completing the trifecta.

With inhuman reserves of physical and mental stamina, McCoy often finds himself the last person standing at the end of any conflict—physical and verbal alike.

His yellow scarf is a tribute to his time with 1st Cavalry Division.

 Yep. Still here.

agents.name: Cmdr. Mae 'Dead Cold' Jamison | SWAT
agents.description: Cmdr. 'Dead Cold' Jamison has just about seen it all. Skeptical and wry in the midst of deadly combat, others could mistake her for being nonchalant about the chaos at hand. They would be wrong. Nothing gets past Dead Cold, not bad guys with AK-47s, junior officers that call her 'Ma'am,' or an opportunity to make elite officers smirk under pressure.\n\n You're gonna find out.

agents.name: 1st Lieutenant Farlow | SWAT
agents.description: Smart as a whip and relentlessly polite, 1st Lieutenant Farlow is one of the most beloved and respected officers in SWAT. A master tactician in hostage and barricade situations, Farlow quickly climbed the SWAT ranks. Don't be fooled by her overwhelmingly cheerful nature--she can dispatch bad guys in the blink of an eye and not think twice about it.\n\n What are they doing over there? Drinking milkshakes?

agents.name: John 'Van Healen' Kask | SWAT
agents.description: John 'Van Healen' Kask is one of SWATs best tactical defence units and on-site military paramedics. He also shreds a mean guitar—sometimes mid-operation. He says it helps get his teammates' blood pumping just as effectively as an AED, which he keeps ready in case of emergency. \n\n I can bring you back to life, but I can't make you live.

agents.name: Bio-Haz Specialist | SWAT
agents.description: The SWAT's Biological Hazard Specialists are trained to handle worst case bio warfare situations. Terrorists planning to unleash a bio hazard attack upon unsuspecting civilians do not want to deal with these guys.\n\n Tacita Sed Mortiferum.

agents.name: Sergeant Bombson | SWAT
agents.description: Tyler Bobson earned his moniker after becoming SWAT's go-to officer for efficient Explosive Ordnance Disposal. With his uncanny ability to locate even the most well hidden IEDs, Bombson's keen hearing is outclassed only by the noble Greater Wax Moth.\n\n Yeah, I heard that.

agents.name: Chem-Haz Specialist | SWAT
agents.description: The SWAT Chemical Hazard Specialists are able to survive and succeed in toxic environment operations for hours at a time. Where others run away, they run in.\n\n Feels like home.

agents.name: Rezan the Redshirt | Sabre
agents.description:
An expert grenadier and the once-celebrated author of The Joy of Preparedness, Rezan the Redshirt is Sabre's self-appointed Head of Operations.

Over time, Rezan has learned to control his fiery temper—now he wears his explosive rage on his sleeves.

 I take great pride in my work.

agents.name: Sir Bloody Miami Darryl | The Professionals
agents.description:
The leader of 'The Professionals' can be described as cocky, wisecracking, and scarily indifferent with regards to the suffering of others. He would say he's just a bloke—a bloke that likes to have a bit of fun on the weekend with the local armed tax collectors. He downplays the severity of any heavy situations that come his way, even if he's the last man standing, riddled with bullets, with only seconds left to blow the safe.

This white hockey mask and floral shirt were popular choices during his Vice phase. 

 Got my hair combed back and my sunglasses on.

agents.name: Safecracker Voltzmann | The Professionals
agents.description: Weird, quirky, unhinged; a few words that describe The Professionals' safecracker and technical mastermind. When she is not mumbling to herself about the flawed assumptions inherent within the profit maximization paradox, Safecracker serves as a morally questionable but highly efficient 'fundraising expert.' She enjoys short walks on pavement, the sound of cable ties being fastened, and testing explosive prototypes under immense pressure.\n\n Don't blow it. DO blow the bomb though, okay? We do want that.

agents.name: Little Kev | The Professionals
agents.description: The Professional who makes heavy weapons look weightless, Little Kev is the soft spoken 'little' brother of Sir Bloody Darryl. His older brother's bodyguard since age 5, Little Kev developed a knack for quelling 'people problems' before they arise. Sir Darryl assigned him Human Resources Manager for the entire Professionals organization.  \n\n We're getting this done either way.

agents.name: Getaway Sally | The Professionals
agents.description: Small enough to hide in plain sight but loud enough to frighten the biggest enemies, Getaway Sally is The Professionals' first pick for tight quarter Wealth Acquisition Projects.  A talented weaver of controlled chaos, Getaway Sally has the improvisational skills to turn the tables on any dire heist and hostage situations. \n\n Now you don't see me, and now you still don't.

agents.name: Number K | The Professionals
agents.description: In his 'Wealth Acquisition Specialist' application form, Number K wrote the letter 'K' in every number field, but his talent with handguns made him more than qualified for the position. Number K keeps the details of his life private—none of his colleagues have seen his face—making him one of The Professionals' most feared heist managers.\n\n Don't count us down. Just say go.

agents.name: Sir Bloody Silent Darryl | The Professionals
agents.description:
The leader of 'The Professionals' can be described as cocky, wisecracking, and scarily indifferent with regards to the suffering of others. He would say he's just a bloke—a bloke that likes to have a bit of fun on the weekend with the local armed tax collectors. He downplays the severity of any heavy situations that come his way, even if he's the last man standing, riddled with bullets, with only seconds left to blow the safe.

This 'Vow of Silence' mask was Darryl's response to organizational complaints about his logorrhea. 

 ...

agents.name: Sir Bloody Skullhead Darryl | The Professionals
agents.description:
The leader of 'The Professionals' can be described as cocky, wisecracking, and scarily indifferent with regards to the suffering of others. He would say he's just a bloke—a bloke that likes to have a bit of fun on the weekend with the local armed tax collectors. He downplays the severity of any heavy situations that come his way, even if he's the last man standing, riddled with bullets, with only seconds left to blow the safe.

This black mask has been painted with a white skull, a useful bit of intimidation back when The Professionals were just getting started. 

 Are we gonna bloody finish this thing or what?!

agents.name: Sir Bloody Darryl Royale | The Professionals
agents.description:
The leader of 'The Professionals' can be described as cocky, wisecracking, and scarily indifferent with regards to the suffering of others. He would say he's just a bloke—a bloke that likes to have a bit of fun on the weekend with the local armed tax collectors. He downplays the severity of any heavy situations that come his way, even if he's the last man standing, riddled with bullets, with only seconds left to blow the safe.

This gold mask with a crown stencil commemorates The Professionals' first visit to Monaco. 

 Do you know what they call a cheeseburger in Monaco?

agents.name: Sir Bloody Loudmouth Darryl | The Professionals
agents.description:
The leader of 'The Professionals' can be described as cocky, wisecracking, and scarily indifferent with regards to the suffering of others. He would say he's just a bloke—a bloke that likes to have a bit of fun on the weekend with the local armed tax collectors. He downplays the severity of any heavy situations that come his way, even if he's the last man standing, riddled with bullets, with only seconds left to blow the safe.

This mask has been painted with clown makeup, perfect for taking candy from rich spoiled babies. 

 ...The crying on the inside kind, I guess.

agents.name: Sous-Lieutenant Medic | Gendarmerie Nationale
agents.description: Medics of the Gendarmerie National have a well-deserved reputation for providing life saving interventions using anything at their disposal. From improvised AEDs to jungle medicine to precise covering fire, the medics of the Gendarm have your back—no matter what. \n\n  It is better to prevent than to heal.

agents.name: Chem-Haz Capitaine | Gendarmerie Nationale
agents.description: As leader for Chemical and BioHazard combat operations in populated areas, the Gendarmerie Chem-Haz Capitaine plays a crucial role within the organization. Celebrated for orchestrating the successful rescue of an entire domestic airport's civilian occupancy in the infamous sarin gas attack of 1997, the Chem-Haz Capitaine is the epitome of preparedness and composure.    \n\n Don't forget to breathe.

agents.name: Chef d'Escadron Rouchard | Gendarmerie Nationale
agents.description: Born into an old aristocratic family, Rouchard enlisted in the Gendarmerie Nationale at her first opportunity as a way to avoid compulsory enrollment at a notorious Swiss finishing school for young women. As Aspirant in the Gendarmerie, Rouchard quickly impressed her senior ranks by excelling in offensive strategy and hostage negotiations, but most of all, blade-based combat. Several promotions later she is best known by her moniker 'Le Couteau' (The Knife), although some would say this is because she can be a bit blunt at times. Today, Rouchard gets called in when no one else knows what to do. \n\n It is but a scratch.

agents.name: Aspirant | Gendarmerie Nationale
agents.description: Aspirants of the Gendarmerie are highly trained military police cadets responsible for assisting in rural combat operations. To say most are eager for action in the field is an understatement.   \n\n C'est la vie.

agents.name: Officer Jacques Beltram | Gendarmerie Nationale
agents.description: A highly decorated Officer for the Gendarmerie, Beltram was awarded the Legion of Honor for swapping places with a hostage and thwarting terrorist activity on more than one occasion. Beltram is a hero, a single father, and a passionate consumer of pain au chocolate at all times of day.  \n\n We do what we have to do.

agents.name: Lieutenant 'Tree Hugger' Farlow | SWAT
agents.description: No one else knows how to enjoy combat ops that require sunscreen, mosquito repellant and M4A4 assault rifles quite like Farlow does. \n\n Kinda nice to get out of the cold don't ya think?

agents.name: Cmdr. Davida 'Goggles' Fernandez | SEAL Frogman
agents.description: Possessing an exquisite mammalian dive reflex, Cmdr. Fernandez is able to slow her heart rate to undetectable levels and navigate darkness, ice, and deep sea defense systems. She excels in her human aquatic potential and her skill as an elite marksman and soldier. 'Goggles' earned her nickname when a bullet struck her left eye—or would have—if it weren't for 'Wet Sox' reminding her to grab her full kit 'for the last time!' Despite her occasional forgetfulness, Cmdr. Fernandez is one of two elite combat diver SEALs to be awarded The Navy Cross for classified underwater operations. \n\n Be still my beating heart.

agents.name: Cmdr. Frank 'Wet Sox' Baroud | SEAL Frogman
agents.description: First on deck and last off it, Cmdr. Frank Baroud is a third generation SEAL and second combat diver ever to receive The Navy Cross medal; 'Goggles' was the first. Count on Baroud to solve the most complicated underwater and ground based conflict situations, like the time he defused several IED's which were planted in a network of flooded caves beneath a US embassy. Baroud chalks it up to his impeccable attention to detail, because after all, when your life depends on the equipment you're wearing, a simple mistake may be the last one you make. His uncompromising attention to detail earned him the nickname 'Wet Sox'.\n\n Double check it. Then triple check it. Then check it again.

agents.name: Lieutenant Rex Krikey | SEAL Frogman
agents.description: Lieutenant Krikey is a prime choice for all jungle and wetlands combat operations. His expertise in handling wild reptiles big and small has saved both him and his fellow frogmen on more than one occasion.\n\n I'm just an apex predator that enjoys meeting other apex predators.

agents.name: Elite Trapper Solman | Guerrilla Warfare
agents.description: On a hot summer day on the outskirt islands of the Caribbean, Solman, relaxing on a small yet expensive vacation tour, was taken hostage by the infamous Guerrilla Warfare (GW). Overhearing his captors talk about the division of ransom money, Solman negotiated his own release if he delivered three additional hostages within 24 hours. And deliver he did, armed with only money, charm, and a way with words reserved for the world's most horrific cult leaders. Stunned by his lack of empathy for his fellow tourists and his ability to deliver a steady supply of 'ransom units' (people) the GW negotiated a position for Solman among them. Taking the highest percentage of hostage random money of any member of the GW, Solman had won the game before it even started.\n\n You only need three things to fix a bad situation: money, charm, and a loaded weapon.

agents.name: Crasswater The Forgotten | Guerrilla Warfare
agents.description: Former Navy SEAL Capt. Crasswater was taken prisoner by the Guerrilla Warfare (GW) while serving in the Middle East during the 1990's. After a botched rescue attempt by ST6 and subsequent military cover-up, the US Navy declared Crasswater deceased. Over the years of his imprisonment, his patriotism and 'no man left behind' mantra eroded into bitter hatred for all things USA. Newly armed with a severe case of Stockholm Syndrome, Crasswater joined the Trappers of the GW. After a series of 'trust building' attacks on western embassies, Crasswater became GW's most valuable asset—bringing military discipline and organization to an otherwise chaotic gang of rebel fighters. In recent years Crasswater has grown new GW cells at undisclosed locations across Central America. \n\n Just one more forget-me-not.

agents.name: Arno The Overgrown | Guerrilla Warfare
agents.description: Disgraced heavyweight boxing champion, Arno The Overgrown was discovered by Guerrilla Warfare (GW) Trappers living out of a cave. Over the years Arno had become an expert survivalist and big-game hunter—able to live off the land for an indefinite amount of time carrying only his flint stick and sharpened hunting knife. Rumors of Arno eventually spread to nearby townships where he came to attention of Guerrilla Warfare (GW). Wanting to recruit Arno's flawless hunting and fighting skills, the GW failed to coax Arno from his habitat, that is, until they threatened to stop visiting him with hot fresh Milk Tarts every month. \n\n It isn't the loneliness that kills you, it's the absence of Melk Tarts.

agents.name: Col. Mangos Dabisi | Guerrilla Warfare
agents.description: Early in his life Col. Mangos Dabisi was trained and promoted within Ugandan military. He ended his military career with a rare Dishonorable Discharge for intimidating his subordinates into paying him 'sleep well money'—promising a good night's sleep to those who paid him. Turns out, a good night's sleep was merely a lack of intentional injuries inflicted by Dabisi himself. Dabisi's imposing stature and military skill made him an attractive acquisition for the Guerrilla Warfare (GW). Constantly over-using force and needing to be reined in, Dabisi's reputation as a GW powerhouse is well deserved.\n\n I chop your doller or your neck. You choose.

agents.name: Vypa Sista of the Revolution | Guerrilla Warfare
agents.description: A notorious rebel and brilliant improviser, Vypa is one of twelve sisters born into poverty and left to fend for themselves at the age of seven. Vypa's solo attacks against her country's military dictatorship were so prolific the military assumed her work was the result of a small team of people. At one point, Vypa mistook a remote Guerrilla Warfare (GW) training ground for a government outpost. Shortly after invoking one of her infamous 'sting and choke' maneuvers on the camp she realized her mistake, but not before she had Capt. Crasswater tied up to a tree and threatened at knife point. Impressed and a little frightened, Crasswater recruited Vypa and her sisters into the GW. Together they now lead all jungle-based GW missions and 'government awareness' campaigns. \n\n Don't worry, it's just me.

agents.name: Trapper Aggressor | Guerrilla Warfare
agents.description: The experienced and cunning Trapper Aggressors utilize ruthless efficiency in capturing and securing tourists as hostages. As experts in wetland and jungle-based guerrilla tactics, any rescue missions involving Trapper Aggressors are doomed to fail. \n\n The promise of air conditioning and iced tea. It works every time.

agents.name: 'Medium Rare' Crasswater | Guerrilla Warfare
agents.description: Former Navy SEAL Capt. Crasswater was taken prisoner by the Guerrilla Warfare (GW) while serving in the Middle East during the 1990's. After a botched rescue attempt by ST6 and subsequent military cover-up, the US Navy declared Crasswater deceased. Over the years of his imprisonment, his patriotism and 'no man left behind' mantra eroded into bitter hatred for all things USA. Newly armed with a severe case of Stockholm Syndrome, Crasswater joined the Trappers of the GW. After a series of 'trust building' attacks on western embassies, Crasswater became GW's most valuable asset—bringing military discipline and organization to an otherwise chaotic gang of rebel fighters. In recent years Crasswater has grown new GW cells at undisclosed locations across Central America. \n\n Just one more forget-me-not.

agents.name: Trapper | Guerrilla Warfare
agents.description: Sharp, stealthy, and the bane of organised military units everywhere, the Trappers are rarely seen before they are felt.  \n\n We hunt you.

agents.name: Ground Rebel  | Elite Crew
agents.description: An expert in local knowledge for Elite Crew's urban operations, Ground Rebels are known for keeping an ear to the ground.\n\n That's the signal.

agents.name: Osiris | Elite Crew
agents.description: Osiris earned his nickname from passing judgement, often too quickly, on his marks.

agents.name: Prof. Shahmat | Elite Crew
agents.description:
After graduating Magna Cum Laude, Prof. Shahmat began teaching to impart knowledge. With every class Shahmat realized his pupils didn't have the same revolutionary desires that he did. 

Recognizing that his mind was beginning to dull, he decided to seek a new challenge—mastering the art of war.

 Watch and learn.

agents.name: The Elite Mr. Muhlik | Elite Crew
agents.description:
First appeared operating as an 'Acquisitions Consultant' for arms industry magnates, Mr. Muhlik quickly worked his way on to many Most Wanted lists worldwide. Unconfirmed reports suggest he is the last surviving heir to a recently-deposed Middle Eastern monarch. 

With evidence of elite military training, international private education, and numerous international bank accounts, it's suspected Mr. Muhlik is maneuvering to rebuild sovereign power over his family's historical lands.

 Pressure and time.

agents.name: Jungle Rebel | Elite Crew
agents.description: Elite Crew's wetland and jungle based ground rebel. Deadly in the shade(s). \n\n It's dark and I'm wearing sunglasses.

agents.name: Soldier | Phoenix
agents.description: A capable shooter recruited by Phoenix to assist with Territory Reclamation Campaigns. Soldiers are extremely deadly alone, and even more so in numbers.\n\n When do we shoot?

agents.name: Enforcer | Phoenix
agents.description: A multidisciplinary contract hitman for the Phoenix Connexion. Enforcers don't take all assignments, just the ones they find interesting.\n\n Time is money.

agents.name: Slingshot | Phoenix
agents.description:
Slingshot is a critical component of Phoenix Connexion's dominance in close-range combat.

Tightly wound and capable of devastating results with little resources, Slingshot earned his nickname after retaking the Phoenix compound with only an M9 Bayonet and recovered weapons.

 If I can knife, I knife.

agents.name: Street Soldier | Phoenix
agents.description: A Phoenix ground force gang with expertise in high density urban environments. Their knowledge of back roads and alleyways are only surpassed by local taxi drivers, which are rumored to make up a significant portion of their numbers.\n\n I know a shortcut.

agents.name: Operator | FBI SWAT
agents.description: Members of the FBI's SWAT team are deployed in high-risk situations. Counterterrorism, hostage rescue, and bomb defusals are a few of the many disciplines FBI SWAT agents specialize in.\n\n Fidelity, Bravery, Integrity.

agents.name: Markus Delrow | FBI HRT
agents.description:
There's no detail too small for Markus Delrow. Equipment, battle plans, oppositional tactics—you name it—and he's already thought of it twice. 

Being two steps ahead is what he does best, and Delrow takes pride in being the brains of the operation.

 All that's left is to execute.

agents.name: Michael Syfers  | FBI Sniper
agents.description:
An ex-Division I athlete, Syfers was recruited by the FBI after a catastrophic knee injury ended his sports career early. Yet even in adversity he remained positive. 

It's rare to find someone whose desire to succeed is matched by their desire to do good, but Syfers checks both boxes.

 Naturally, I finished my reps.

agents.name: Special Agent Ava | FBI
agents.description:
Initially underestimated, Special Agent Ava soon became her team's ultimate secret weapon. 

Despite receiving three out of five possible FBI Honorary Medals, Ava is surprisingly indifferent to her accomplishments. The way she sees it, it's nothing compared to growing up with four older brothers in urban New Jersey. 

Special Agent Ava takes pleasure from the simple things: clean wins, cold beer, and turning bad guys into thin crust pizza pie. 

 They see me. They're confused. And then they're dead.

agents.name: 3rd Commando Company | KSK
agents.description: An elite soldier from Germany's Kommando Spezialkräfte, members of 3rd Commando Company are hand-picked to be part of KSK's Operational Forces.\n\n This is not relevant to the task at hand.

agents.name: Seal Team 6 Soldier | NSWC SEAL
agents.description: Combat-ready and hungry for wins, SEAL Team 6 soldiers know how to get the job done.\n\n I'm just happy to be here.

agents.name: Buckshot | NSWC SEAL
agents.description: Known as SEAL Team's \"WeaponsSommelier\" Buckshot has thoroughly field-tested and reviewed almost every available military weapon in staggering depth. ST6 relies on Buckshot's knowledge of lesser-known guns for edge case advantages in ground based operations—but in the interest of time, they strenuously avoid casual conversation on the topic.\n\n They talk to me. The guns. They have feelings.

agents.name: 'Two Times' McCoy | USAF TACP
agents.description:
'Two Times' McCoy earned his nickname by completing TACP's field training twice. Official records mark this up to a scheduling mix-up, but his teammates report restraining him from completing the trifecta.

With inhuman reserves of physical and mental stamina, McCoy often finds himself the last person standing at the end of any conflict—physical and verbal alike. 

 Yep. Still here.

agents.name: Lt. Commander Ricksaw | NSWC SEAL
agents.description:
Lt. Commander Ricksaw's comically laissez-faire attitude toward heavy combat keeps his SEAL team calm and deadly in the most dire situations. 

Having lead more special ops than any other SEAL to date, Ricksaw knows life is short, and encourages his team to make the most of the time they have—including cheerfully serving up bullets and frag grenades to high- value targets at any and all occasions.

 Hotdogs, hellcats and hand grenades. Hooya!

agents.name: Primeiro Tenente | Brazilian 1st Battalion
agents.description: As a combat survival specialist in deep jungle operations, the Brazilian 1st Battalion sharpen their teeth alongside the banks of the mighty Amazon River.   \n\n Surprises welcome.

agents.name: Dragomir | Sabre
agents.description: A man of few words, Dragomir is disturbingly patient. Known for holding position for days at a time, some say he's one of Sabre's best marksman. Others say he's napping. No one really knows. No one left alive, anyway.\n\n ...I wait.

agents.name: Maximus | Sabre
agents.description: Motivated by a simmering inner rage and a lifelong obsession with vengeance for transgressions large, small, and seemingly insignificant, Maximus is Sabre's first choice for close quarter mission support. No grudge is too small to be repaid in blood.\n\n No, YOU overreacted.

agents.name: Rezan The Ready | Sabre
agents.description:
An expert grenadier and the once-celebrated author of The Joy of Preparedness, Rezan The Ready is Sabre's self-appointed Head of Operations.

His fiery temper when things get out of hand has earned him the alternative nickname Rezan the Red—but never to his face.

 I take great pride in my work.

agents.name: Blackwolf | Sabre
agents.description: Blackwolf stalks Sabre's enemies with preternatural determination and focus. Raised deep within the bitter forests of Eastern Europe, he can sense human presence with exceptional accuracy—and he knows what to do when he's sensed it. \n\n I don't need to see them to kill them.

agents.name: 'The Doctor' Romanov | Sabre
agents.description: After expertly smuggling pharmaceuticals across disputed borders for over 30 years, the 'doctor' now leads Sabre's Utility Disruption Operations. Rumoured to be responsible for the synchronized destruction of several UN power facilities, Romanov is known by his enemies to be calculating, deliberate, and frighteningly precise. Of course, his mother says he's just mixed up with the wrong crowd.\n\n It's simple. We make a plan and the plan is to win.

agents.name: Dragomir | Sabre Footsoldier
agents.description: Sabre has noticed that enemies seem to die quite frequently around Dragomir, even though they've never actually seen him shoot his gun. They're happy to keep him around... for now. \n\n ...I wait.

agents.name: B Squadron Officer | SAS
agents.description: Highly classified and incredibly lethal, Officers in the SAS spend years sharpening their skills through infiltration, hostage rescue, and —REDACTED— missions not fit for the public eye.\n\n Who dares, wins.

agents.name: D Squadron Officer | NZSAS
agents.description: Highly classified and incredibly lethal, Officers in the SAS spend years sharpening their skills through infiltration, hostage rescue, and —REDACTED— missions not fit for the public eye.\n\n Who dares, wins.

music_kits.name: Music Kit | Daniel Sadowski, Crimson Assault
music_kits.description: Video Game Composer Daniel Sadowski delivers Edgy Action mixed with CRAZY FAT beats in this pulsating, exhilarating Music Pack.

music_kits.name: Music Kit | Noisia, Sharpened
music_kits.description: Dutch Electronic Trio Noisia brings a tough, cinematic feel with a unique blend of tradition and progression.

music_kits.name: Music Kit | Robert Allaire, Insurgency
music_kits.description: Music to crush your enemies see them driven before you from award winning composer Robert Allaire.

music_kits.name: Music Kit | Sean Murray, A*D*8
music_kits.description: From the composer of two of the world's biggest war games, comes a sonic loadout that will bring your enemies to Hell's Gate!!

music_kits.name: Music Kit | Feed Me, High Noon
music_kits.description: Renowned elecronic musician Feed Me, brings a western corral showdown into a modern electronic space.

music_kits.name: Music Kit | Dren, Death's Head Demolition
music_kits.description: From game music composer Dren, this cinematic, superhero-metal inspired music pack puts the 'ill' into KILL!

music_kits.name: Music Kit | Austin Wintory, Desert Fire
music_kits.description: Grammy nominated game composer Austin Wintory asks, why bother hunting your enemies when you can lure them in with a deadly, admittedly insane, tango?

music_kits.name: Music Kit | Sasha, LNOE
music_kits.description: Immerse yourself in this cinematic soundtrack full of soaring strings, pulsating melodies and driving drums from the world renowned DJ / Producer Sasha

music_kits.name: Music Kit | Skog, Metal
music_kits.description: A lesson in aggression from Metal producer, Skog.

music_kits.name: Music Kit | Midnight Riders, All I Want for Christmas
music_kits.description: HAPPYHOLIDAYS - Midnight Riders

music_kits.name: Music Kit | Matt Lange, IsoRhythm
music_kits.description: Indulge your aural senses in a collection of cinematic, glitchy atmospheres and hard-hitting throbbing rhythms by electronic producer and innovator Matt Lange.

music_kits.name: Music Kit | Mateo Messina, For No Mankind
music_kits.description: Own your enemies. Pure intensity by Grammy winning composer, Mateo Messina.

music_kits.name: Music Kit | Various Artists, Hotline Miami
music_kits.description: A multitude of electronic artists deliver brutal beats in this exhilarating Music Pack from the iconic Hotline Miami.

music_kits.name: Music Kit | Daniel Sadowski, Total Domination
music_kits.description: Composer Daniel Sadowski raises the bar with aggressive electronic beats, creative sound fx and an exhilerating, driving, futuristic vibe. \"Warning: Willcauseariseinadrenaline!\"

music_kits.name: Music Kit | Damjan Mravunac, The Talos Principle
music_kits.description: Composer Damjan Mravunac blends energetic cinematic grooves with epic choirs in this music pack featuring music from Croteam's critically acclaimed title \"TheTalosPrinciple\".

music_kits.name: Music Kit | Proxy, Battlepack
music_kits.description: Russian Heavy Electronica Artist PROXY brings his own Unique heavy artillery to Counter Strike. Hybrid audio Weaponry fused with the finest studio technology makes this pack unique.

music_kits.name: Music Kit | Ki:Theory, MOLOTOV
music_kits.description: Recording artist and DOTA TI4 performer, Ki:Theory drops BOMBS with this searing set of razor edge dark electronic rock.

music_kits.name: Music Kit | Troels Folmann, Uber Blasto Phone
music_kits.description: Triumphant Blastophones combine with contemporary Uberpulse in this explosive collection by ultra award winning composer Troels Folmann.

music_kits.name: Music Kit | Kelly Bailey, Hazardous Environments
music_kits.description: Kelly Bailey, composer of Valve's Half-Life series, creates an arsenal of apocalyptic new music inspired by the darker side of the Half-Life universe.

music_kits.name: Music Kit | Skog, II-Headshot
music_kits.description: Metal composer and producer Jocke Skog returns with an all new, hard hitting metal kit, turning the rest of the CS:GO Music Kits into something cute, warm and fuzzy. Now go become MVP so everyone can hear your awesomeness!

music_kits.name: Music Kit | Daniel Sadowski, The 8-Bit Kit
music_kits.description: Daniel Sadowski creates the first ever 8-bit Music Kit for Counter-Strike complete with authentic 8-bit sounds.

music_kits.name: Music Kit | AWOLNATION, I Am
music_kits.description: AWOLNATION Alternative Rocker AWOLNATION brings you a music kit for the ages. This kit is jam-packed with an eclectic selection of tunes and includes cuts from singles 'I Am' and multi-platinum hit 'Sail'.

music_kits.name: Music Kit | Mord Fustang, Diamonds
music_kits.description: Diamonds. They are forever. Dive into the arpeggiotron of Mord Fustang with this fresh set of grooves and atmospheres.

music_kits.name: Music Kit | Michael Bross, Invasion!
music_kits.description: Michael Bross conjures epic / cinematic techno-grunge to make you feel like a true badass in battle.

music_kits.name: Music Kit | Ian Hultquist, Lion's Mouth
music_kits.description: Mixing pulsating strings and synths with pounding war drums, prepare yourself for battle with this thunderous soundtrack from composer Ian Hultquist.

music_kits.name: Music Kit | New Beat Fund, Sponge Fingerz
music_kits.description: Sunny surf rock with elements of hip-hop, punk and garage pop. Keep it real and get headshots.

music_kits.name: Music Kit | Beartooth, Disgusting
music_kits.description: Beartooth brings an agressive back-to-basics hardcore stomp that gets crowds moving and breaking stuff. A perfect soundtrack for your no-scope scout frags. Rock 'till you're dead.

music_kits.name: Music Kit | Lennie Moore, Java Havana Funkaloo
music_kits.description: Game Composer Lennie Moore serves an aromatic, spicy blend of Jazzy Funk. Delicious when served cold, like the corpses of your enemies after you're done with them.

music_kits.name: Music Kit | Darude, Moments CS:GO
music_kits.description: Yield freely in the soundscapes of Finnish producer Darude's familiar musical flavours and tones. Enriching yourself with access to a heavy fusion of progressive overtones and scores of tingling melodic structure from the sounds banks of one of dance music's most renowned pioneers.

music_kits.name: Music Kit | Beartooth, Aggressive
music_kits.description: Beartooth is back for round two. This new music kit hits harder and is even more aggressive. We've also made the MVP anthem extra heavy so your opponents feel really bad after they've lost to you.

music_kits.name: Music Kit | Blitz Kids, The Good Youth
music_kits.description: British Pop/Punk band Blitz Kids brings you the perfect music kit for rushing B while thinking about those night drives you had with your friends in High School. This kit is for going fast and feeling young.

music_kits.name: Music Kit | Hundredth, FREE
music_kits.description: Hundredth is bringing heavy to the world with their unique take on melodic hardcore. Break free or return to Dust with this perfect soundtrack for fragging the unworthy.

music_kits.name: Music Kit | Neck Deep, Life's Not Out To Get You
music_kits.description: Sometimes you just need some Pop Punk to get you through the day. Whether it is dealing with campers or losing a massive kill streak, Neck Deep is here to prove that Life's Not Out To Get You, but the other team still is.

music_kits.name: Music Kit | Roam, Backbone
music_kits.description: Roam delivers fast, straight-forward Pop Punk that gets crowd and players alike moving. Prove you have a Backbone with this perfect soundtrack for rushing in and obliterating the other team before they even realize they're deadweight.

music_kits.name: Music Kit | Twin Atlantic, GLA
music_kits.description: Heavier, rowdier, and louder than ever, Twin Atlantic comes to CS:GO ready to help you melt the faces with the firepower of Scottish rock.

music_kits.name: Music Kit | Skog, III-Arena
music_kits.description: Skog is back with a third crushing metal kit. This time with an electro-organic twist to the music, combining massive guitar riffs with equally massive drops, loop elements and drones.

music_kits.name: Music Kit | The Verkkars, EZ4ENCE
music_kits.description: The Verkkars rise through the Finnish charts with a heart-pounding tribute to ENCE. Can it really be so EZ?

music_kits.name: Halo, The Master Chief Collection
music_kits.description: Give your Counter Strike auditory experience a legendary makeover with the Master Chief Collection Music Pack, featuring iconic musical moments from the Halo universe. © 2019 343 Industries. All rights reserved. Used with permission from 343 Industries. Halo: The Master Chief Collection and the Halo logo are trademarks of the Microsoft group of companies.

music_kits.name: Music Kit | Scarlxrd: King, Scar
music_kits.description: Scarlxrd blends heavy trap beats with a flow and delivery that creates his own unique subgenre. With this exciting blend his live shows capture the attention of everyone in the crowd.

music_kits.name: Half-Life: Alyx, Anti-Citizen
music_kits.description: This music kit commemorates Half-Life: Alyx, Valve's VR return to the Half-Life series. You are humanity's only chance for survival, and your immersive environmental interactions continue in Counter-Strike: Global Offensive.

music_kits.name: Music Kit | Austin Wintory, Bachram
music_kits.description: Austin Wintory mixes Celtic fantasy with sizzling electronics and a generous helping of Peter Hollens' vocals in this genre-bending Music Kit.

music_kits.name: Music Kit | Dren, Gunman Taco Truck
music_kits.description: The apocalyptic mariachi soundtrack from the indie game hit, Gunman Taco Truck, comes to CS:GO with intense Mexican flavored tunes like Pollo Diablo and Persecución de Helltain!

music_kits.name: Music Kit | Daniel Sadowski, Eye of the Dragon
music_kits.description: From the composer who brought you \"TotalDomination\", \"The8-BitKit\" and \"CrimsonAssault\", comes \"EyeOfTheDragon\". Music composer Daniel Sadowski mixes Ninjas + Guns + Hip-Hop + Techno to create an action-packed Music Kit.  Ninjas are known for their fast and precise attacks, yet they can be invisible to their enemy.

music_kits.name: Music Kit | Tree Adams and Ben Bromfield, M.U.D.D. FORCE
music_kits.description: Alchemists of a powerful chaos that is M.U.D.D. FORCE - composers Tree Adams and Ben Bromfield weld epic battle motifs and grinding synths into a Maelstrom of full throttle destruction.

music_kits.name: Music Kit | Tim Huling, Neo Noir
music_kits.description: Composer Tim Huling delivers classic film-noir style tracks blended with contemporary grooves and beats.

music_kits.name: Music Kit | Sam Marshall, Bodacious
music_kits.description: Inspired by the funky video game music of the early 90s, composer Sam Marshall cooks up some classic game nostalgia with a spicy modern sauce.

music_kits.name: Music Kit | Matt Levine, Drifter
music_kits.description: Composer Matt Levine delivers raw swagger in this gritty homage to the Spaghetti Western.

music_kits.name: Music Kit | Amon Tobin, All for Dust
music_kits.description: Legendary producer Amon Tobin lends his unique aesthetic to CS:GO. This time through tube amplifiers.

music_kits.name: Darren Korb, Hades Music Kit
music_kits.description: Sure, you might miss a shot from time to time, but what never misses is this blood-pumping Music Kit straight from the Underworld of Hades, Supergiant's rogue-like dungeon crawler.

music_kits.name: Music Kit | Neck Deep, The Lowlife Pack
music_kits.description: Prove you are not a normie (and better than everyone else on the map) with Neck Deep's new music kit, which includes songs from the band's album All Distortions Are Intentional.

music_kits.name: Music Kit | Scarlxrd, CHAIN$AW.LXADXUT.
music_kits.description: CHAIN$AW BRINGS SCARLXRD AT HIS UNPRECENDENTED BEST WITH A RAW FLOW AND A HEAVY TRACK TO MATCH.

music_kits.name: Music Kit | Austin Wintory, Mocha Petal
music_kits.description: Austin Wintory answers the question humanity has asked for ages: what happens if you merge beer garden accordion polka music with grungy heavy metal?

music_kits.name: Music Kit | Chipzel, ~Yellow Magic~
music_kits.description: Video game composer and chiptune legend Chipzel brings a glitchy Speak & Spell inspired mashup of hybrid styles packed with fun, funk and flavour.

music_kits.name: Music Kit | Freaky DNA, Vici
music_kits.description: Opera. 8-bit sounds. Analogue synths. What's not to love? Chiptune specialist Freaky DNA and soprano Leanne Koch team up for some heavy beats and good times!

music_kits.name: Music Kit | Jesse Harlin, Astro Bellum
music_kits.description: Composer Jesse Harlin delivers bombastic space opera drama inspired by classic sci-fi of the 70s, 80s, and beyond.

music_kits.name: Music Kit | Laura Shigihara: Work Hard, Play Hard
music_kits.description: Video game composer and developer Laura Shigihara will help you tell everyone loudly and proudly that you're the MVP. Have fun with this unique blend of 90s dance, retro video game synth, and just a hint of Plants vs. Zombies.

music_kits.name: Music Kit | Sarah Schachner, KOLIBRI
music_kits.description: Brought to you by Sarah Schachner, a dystopian goth choir of self-aware, Scandinavian robots decide that humanity must be eliminated.

music_kits.name: Music Kit | bbno$, u mad!
music_kits.description: bbno$ formulates 'the' toxic gamer anthem, u mad! Are u mad? LOL get good scrub. Research shows if you play with this Music Kit equipped you'll immediately go from Silver to Global.

music_kits.name: Music Kit | The Verkkars & n0thing, Flashbang Dance
music_kits.description: From sunny California to frigid Lapland, Counter-Strike legend n0thing and The Verkkars combine powers to create the smash hit, Flashbang Dance! 3, 2, 1 you’re blind!

music_kits.name: Music Kit | 3kliksphilip, Heading for the Source
music_kits.description: On a quest to go pro, or unintentionally going low? Let this kit’s 80’s synths and dreamy melodies take you back. Back, back, back... to the good old days.

music_kits.name: Music Kit | Humanity's Last Breath, Void
music_kits.description: Swedish Band Humanity's Last Breath drops in heavy with their Void Music Kit. Pounding drums, colossal riffs and an atmosphere to send shivers up your spine.

music_kits.name: Music Kit | Juelz, Shooters
music_kits.description: Neo trap synths, gritty 808s, an epic piano riff, and a plethora of gunfire sound effects. The OG trap anthem \"Shooters\" by Juelz makes for a truly elite Music Kit. Suitable for MVPs only.

music_kits.name: Music Kit | Knock2, dashstar*
music_kits.description: dashstar*, the iconic bass house anthem from Knock2, provides non-stop energy that captures the young San Diego native’s mantra, \"nolimit\".

music_kits.name: Music Kit | Meechy Darko, Gothic Luxury
music_kits.description: Grab a Glock and equip this music kit to be transported to the center of New York's underground hip-hop scene.

music_kits.name: Music Kit | Sullivan King, Lock Me Up
music_kits.description: Love the chase? Love the hunt? Hard rock, metal, and dubstep collide in Sullivan King's soundtrack for becoming unstoppable.

music_kits.name: Music Kit | Perfect World, 花脸 Hua Lian (Painted Face)
music_kits.description: Celebrate the 5th anniversary of CS:GO's release in China with a one of a kind music kit, 花脸 Hua Lian (Painted Face). This kit combines folk Qinqiang opera (the earliest Chinese style Rock 'n' Roll) and modern Rock 'n' Roll. Whether you are engulfed in smoke or blinded by a flashbang, don't get lost!
